description: test
Halfway through construction, yes it required nearly six chocolate bars to cover.
I cheated and used brownie Mix this time.
Yeah, this is what\'s on there, had two left over, whatever will I do with them?
The light bits are the Cadbury\'s chocolate and toffee.
All the things we came away with. Not pictured: two swag bags, well used, and a framed print.

The pins are for Corset Inspector and Tesla Rangers. We talked a long time to who must have been Kaja Foglio, who was very nice and personable, although she kept reminding us we could read the whole thing online. (You can read the whole series here): http://www.girlgeniusonline.com/
Completely out of money by the time we got to this booth, but I picked up a card because I liked the concept: http://battlepug.com/

This was a free handout. People had lots of them, but I didn\'t want to presume. Pretty cute.
http://buttersafe.com/

The first person we talked to was Scott Kurtz, stationed with Kris Straub. Taylor got his book signed and sketched, and I got this one. To feel like I was participating
http://chainsawsuit.com/
Upon reading, I am sure I will know what this is all about.

I was interested in a book called Carry On Carrion: A Crow Funeral, but Taylor fell in love with a drawing of a jackalope and bought the original. We got the book to go along with it.
http://www.reidpsaltis.com/

A collection of one-off comics about whatever the artist thought of when they heard \"Bear fight.\"
http://www.banneryearpress.com/bearfight/

I loved the black and white style of these comics, which are almost to the point of being combined into a trade. One of the friendliest signers there.
http://www.webcomicsnation.com/skorpen/moths/

Of course we were going to get Axe Cop. The artist was on his cellphone the whole time, but I think this was just unfortunate timing.
http://axecop.com/

This guy was wearing a costume. I should have taken a picture then. Excited about the artwork in this one, which is really old-school.
http://www.unemployedman.com/

After Taylor threatened to punch Scott Kurtz for giving him the PAX pox two years ago, he was still nice enough to sign and sketch this greatest hits collection.
http://www.pvponline.com/

Considering that his comic has been optioned for a movie, Richard Starkings was certainly gracious.
http://www.hipflask.com/
Look at the sketches he drew!
So much artistry. Really, people behind us were getting bored.
We talked about the Portland rain. He said \"I\'m from England, where we invented the weather.\"
waiting to be devoured
The worst Macbeth adaptation ever!
I was trying to not look at camera.
Showing my school pride
At this bar, the challenge was to combine two random mixed drinks.
The women we challenged to Never Ever. I won, having a good quarter glass of beer when everyone else was dry
Talking to our head of house.
Carl!
Me at 14 in a kimono my grandparents bought on a mission in Japan.
